			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What do bards want?<a name="25733"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 5 04 1:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I will usually wait a pull or two before I start pulling with a MR debuff.  I prefer to pull with a Cancel Magic song, because it has much lower aggro.  If you have trouble landing your slow, ask your Bard puller if they can pull with an MR debuff.  Higher level bards have Occlusion of Sound.  Lower level bards (30+) have Fufill's Curtailing Chant, a Magic based DoT that has an MR debuff.  Our mezzes also have MR debuff, so landing a slow on a mezzed mob should be easier too.
<br />

<br />
I usually don't waste a song slot for Slow when someone else is slowing.  (A good bard is always maximizing their impact by providing what the group does NOT have, hehe).  My only tip would be to use /assist on your bard puller, and land the slow as soon as you can.  The only time I am tempted to use up my song slot for slowing is when it seems to take half the fight for the other slower to land theirs.
<br />

<br />
I melee.  Haste me.  Nothing pisses me off more than having to beg for haste when other classes do not.  Chanters seem to do this more often than Shammies though.
<br />

<br />
If I am NOT going to melee, I will tell you not to waste mana hasting me.   (Sometimes I instrument twist Rune/Regen in a group, especially if healing power is low.  i.e. non-cleric healer, lower level than others in the group, no KEI etc.)
<br />

<br />
Niv's Melody of Preservation and that d*mn wincing thing:
<br />

<br />
If I do a Rune/Regen twist, I will often twist my HP/Mana song with Niv's.  Nivs is a magic damage absorption song.  It DOES eat the damage when you guys cannibalize (and it has some HP regen too).  To maximize the benefit, do NOT chain cast your cannibalize.  Do it every 10 seconds or so, and it is likely you won't even notice any HP loss.
<br />

<br />
Buffs I like, in order of priority:
<br />

<br />
CHA (Reduces likelihood of aggro when a Lull is resisted)
<br />
AGI (Damage avoidance, Defense skillups)
<br />
STA/HP (Dying sucks)
<br />
DEX (Procs, fewer &quot;Missed Notes&quot; (Bard fizzles), weapon skillups)
<br />
STR (more melee damage)
<br />

<br />
If you plan to duo kite with a Bard, I have a whole other list of tips.  Let me know if you want em.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Scherzo Glissando <BR>
