			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What do bards want?<a name="25735"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 5 04 1:54 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In single group situations these days, it usually means we're in a hard LDON or in GoD.  Mobs there hit extremely hard so slowing on the pull really makes a huge difference. I tend to pull with HOS and then land slow on the way back.  If I am pulling casters, I try to pull with a DoT which sometimes seems to make them move sooner.  I still try to land slow before they get to our group.  My regular XP group includes a very tough ogre shaman with over 200 AAs.  He tends to slow early and DoT hard so he usually draws agro for at least part of the battle.  It helps him if I have mobs pre-slowed because he does get resists once in awhile.
<br />

<br />
As for what buffs I want from a shaman -- Focus, Boar and a charisma buff.  In that order, too.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443370">Steppy Astravox</a><br>
