				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;I usually don't waste a song slot for Slow when someone else is slowing.(A good bard is always maximizing their impact by providing what the group does NOT have, hehe). &quot;
<br />

<br />
I disagree with you here Klappy.  I always pull mobs to the camp with my slow. Well, not always, sometimes I seem to have bad resist days so Ill hoS and then instantly cast Slow as i bring the mob to the camp. The extra 50% slow might save a round of damage during the whole fight, but that could still amount to 1k+ worth of healing that was not needed. Plus if the shammie gets resisted at all it will amount to a whole lot more healing saved.
<br />

<br />
I will always pull with HoS then slow or Slow then HoS. even with HoS i've seen shammies get resists on slow and if ours has landed its a big help. rune might save 200damage one cast of slow could save 1k or more.
<br />

<br />
Of course this DOES depend on your level, at lower levels its not such a big deal =).
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
OOh and to get on topic... I like a good tank who can get aggro fast.. the shaman to slow immediately if possible. To backup heal the cleric.. DoT if mana is good.. remember to send in his pet (seen so many shammies forget their puppies). Keep the buffs up (acumen for your human bards pleeease =). thats bout it =)
<br />

