				<td colspan="2"><span>I love me a shammy in my group! The best support in normal grouping situations (normal LDoN's, and... wherever else we go) the best support I can think of is a Druid and a Shaman.. Druid on heals and a good bit of damage (we tend not to need a lot of healing) and a Shammy to keep up the buffage, keep up the haste (Depending on level, on most levels it's a lot better than ours, but I was suprised to find that at least somewhere in the mid 50's our hastes are equally fast, odd...), do the slows, do some more dottage.. Basically have the support in my group be able to do a fair amount of damage as well.. I find it helps immensely in the overal scheme of things.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
That way, all I need in a group is me, a tank and two random DPS, be it mana or melee. Which fits my regular group like a glove, which is 65WAR (or 57 SHM, his alt), 61NEC, 61SHD, 59BST and me, 61BRD.. Very often a 62DRU is online as well, so he rounds out the group very nicely. 
<br />

<br />
But I'm blabbering. I'm really happy with shammies, as for what buffs.. It's been said above.. I love me some CHA, I love the haste, as it allows me to play something instead of my haste song, and the usual combat stats to make me less squishy during pulling/CC'ing and the odd bit of meleeing are more than welcome.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
